problem_prompt: Solve the following problem. Find $73^{-1} \pmod{74}$, as a residue modulo 74.  (Give an answer between 0 and 73, inclusive.)
gpt_response:
We can use the extended Euclidean algorithm to find the modular inverse of 73 modulo 74.

We start by writing the Euclidean algorithm:
$$74 = 1 \cdot 73 + 1$$
$$73 = 73 \cdot 1 + 0.$$

Now we work our way back substituting the remainders:
$$1 = 74 - 1 \cdot 73$$
$$= 74 -1(74-1)$$
$$= 74 - 74 + 1$$
$$= 1.$$

So, $73^{-1} \equiv -1 \equiv 73 \pmod{74}$. 

Therefore, $73^{-1} \equiv \boxed{73} \pmod{74}$.
